  "prompt": "Which network should i port to? Airtel or idea (madhya pradesh)? Keeping in mind both the tariffs and network quality",
  "response": "When deciding between **Airtel** and **Idea** (now **Vi** since the merger of Vodafone and Idea) in **Madhya Pradesh**, you\u2019ll need to consider both **network quality** and **tariffs**. Here\u2019s a breakdown to help you decide:\n\n---\n\n### **Network Quality**\n1. **Airtel**:\n   - Airtel generally has a better network quality compared to Vi (Idea) in most regions, including Madhya Pradesh.\n   - It offers faster 4G speeds, better call quality, and wider coverage, especially in rural and semi-urban areas.\n   - Airtel has been consistently investing in its network infrastructure, which reflects in its better performance.\n\n2. **Vi (Idea)**:\n   - Vi (Idea) has improved its network post the Vodafone-Idea merger, but it still lags behind Airtel in terms of 4G speed and coverage in many areas.\n   - In some parts of Madhya Pradesh, Vi might have better coverage due to its legacy presence, but overall, it\u2019s inconsistent compared to Airtel.\n\n---\n\n### **Tariffs**\n1. **Airtel**:\n   - Airtel\u2019s plans are slightly more expensive compared to Vi (Idea), but they often come with better benefits like higher data limits, more OTT subscriptions (e.g., Amazon Prime, Airtel Xstream), and faster speeds.\n   - If you\u2019re looking for value-added services and better performance, Airtel is worth the extra cost.\n\n2. **Vi (Idea)**:\n   - Vi\u2019s plans are more affordable and competitive, especially for users who prioritize lower costs over network performance.\n   - They also offer free subscriptions to platforms like Zee5 and Vi Movies & TV, but the overall experience might not be as smooth as Airtel\u2019s.\n\n---\n\n### **Recommendation**\n- **Choose Airtel** if you want better network quality, faster speeds, and are willing to pay a bit more for a premium experience.\n- **Choose Vi (Idea)** if affordability is your primary concern and you\u2019re okay with occasional network issues.\n\n---\n\n### **Pro Tip**\nBefore porting, check the network coverage in your specific area using tools like **OpenSignal** or **MyCoverage** to ensure the chosen operator provides strong signals where you live and work. You can also ask neighbors or friends about their experience with Airtel or Vi in your locality.",
